    <body>
      <div xml:id="NA373-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">itu ceṟippaṟivuṟīiyatu.</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">This is what informed about confinement.</p>
        </div>
      <div xml:id="NA373">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            muṉṟiṟ palaviṉ paṭucuḷai marīip</l>
<l>            puṉṟalai manti tūrppat tantai</l>
<l>            maipaṭu mālvarai pāṭiṉaḷ koṭicci</l>
<l>            yaivaṉa veṇṇeṟ kuṟūu nāṭaṉoṭu</l>
<l>            cūruṭaic cilampi ṉaruvi yāṭik</l>
<l>            kārarum paviḻnta kaṇivāy vēṅkaip</l>
<l>            pāvamai yitaṇa mēṟip pāciṉam</l>
<l>            vaṇarkuraṟ ciṟutiṉai kaṭiyap</l>
<l>            puṇarvatu kollō nāḷaiyu namakkē.</l>
            </lg>
        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>            Will [there be] uniting for us, friend, also tomorrow,</l>
<l rend="indent3">            when chasing away from the little millet with curved ears</l>
<l rend="indent">            the green flocks, having mounted the broad bamboo platform</l>
<l rend="indent">            on the Vēṅkai, the mouth of an astrologer, that opened [its] black(?)<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">kār</term> is a problem here. "Rainy season" does not fit, since <term xml:lang="ta">Vēṅkai</term> does not blossom in the rainy season (nor does millet ripen then). <term xml:lang="ta">Vēṅkai</term> buds are for sure not "black". So we are left with the possibility of some vague metaphorical extension like "wet" or "fresh".</note> buds,</l>
<l rend="indent">            [when] playing in the waterfall on the fearful mountain-side</l>
<l rend="indent">            with the man from a land, where the white paddy of wild rice is pounded</l>
<l rend="indent2">            by the creeper woman, who sang(?)<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">pāṭiṉaḷ</term>: here we find once more the deeply unsatisfactory variant of <term xml:lang="ta">muṟṟeccam</term>. But what else to do?</note> of the mountain black</l>
<l rend="indent2">            with collyrium [clouds] of [her] father, 	</l>
<l rend="indent3">            while the low-headed she-monkey approaches the pulp</l>
<l rend="indent3">            coming from the jack-tree in the front yard [and] fills [herself] up?</l>
        </lg>
      </div>
